    - CustomMetadata spectrum_count == number of emitted spectra; spectrum_data_point_count == total emitted point rows.
    - spectrum_array_index JSON declares "sorting_rank":0 on the point.mz entry.
  </behavior>
  <action>
    Replace the single-spectrum scan-down loop and `BuildDataFacet(masses,intensities)` in
    `Write` with a real per-scan loop mirroring `ParquetSpectrumWriter.Write` over
    [firstScanNumber, lastScanNumber]. For each scan: get level via
    `raw.GetScanEventForScanNumber(scanNumber).MSOrder`; skip when `level > MaxLevel` or
    `!MsLevel.Contains(level)`; wrap per-scan work in try/catch calling `ParseInput.NewError()`
    on failure (same as the existing writers). Read points with
    `ReadMZData(raw, scanEvent, scanNumber, !ParseInput.NoPeakPicking.Contains((int)scanFilter.MSOrder), false, false)`.
    For each emitted spectrum, build f64 mz[] and f32 intensity[] arrays, then apply an explicit
    STABLE sort keyed on mz (use a stable approach such as index-decorated OrderBy or a manual
    stable merge over (mz,intensity) pairs) so equal-m/z points retain input order and the
    multiset is preserved — never deduplicate or merge. Append the sorted pairs to growing
    spectrum_index (ulong, the dense 0-based ordinal), mz (double), and intensity (float)
    accumulators; increment the ordinal once per emitted spectrum. After the loop, build the
    point-struct facet (reuse the existing `point` StructField schema, `Leaf`, and `WriteFacet`)
    from the accumulators in a single MemoryStream. Set CustomMetadata `spectrum_count` to the
    emitted-spectrum count and `spectrum_data_point_count` to the total point count. Extend the
    `SpectrumArrayIndex` const so the `point.mz` entry includes `"sorting_rank":0`. Drop the
    "1 spectrum" placeholder log; log real spectrum/point totals. Keep STORED-zip packaging and
    the existing `BuildMetadataFacet`/`BuildIndex` calls (metadata stays Phase-1 minimal —
    leave index/id/time as-is for now; counts in the data facet are the deliverable here).
    Note in code structure (not a comment): accumulating full f64/f32 arrays in memory is
    acceptable for the prototype; record in the SUMMARY whether you added row-group batching
    (flush a row group every ~1,048,576 points, keeping each spectrum whole) or deferred it with
    rationale — the existing ParquetSpectrumWriter flushes at 1_048_576 as the reference cadence.
  </action>
