<threat_model>
## Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| RAW file → writer | Vendor binary scan data (masses/intensities) crosses into our arrays |
| writer → Parquet/ZIP | Numeric arrays serialized to on-disk facets read by external readers |

## STRIDE Threat Register

| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| T-02-01 | Tampering | per-spectrum m/z sort | mitigate | Stable (mz,intensity) sort; NUnit Task-3 (a) asserts multiset preserved (no drop/merge) under duplicate m/z |
| T-02-02 | Information disclosure | f64→f32 intensity narrowing | accept | Lossy narrowing is the declared canonical width (DATA-02); Phase-4 records the transform for L2 round-trip tolerance |
| T-02-03 | Denial of service | full-array accumulation for large RAW | mitigate | Reference cadence is ParquetSpectrumWriter's 1,048,576-point row-group flush; Task 1 either implements per-row-group flushing (spectra kept whole) or records the deferral rationale in SUMMARY |
| T-02-04 | Tampering | centroid/profile routing | mitigate | Route on explicit `MZData.isCentroided` (the representation flag), never inferred from array shape — matches MzMlSpectrumWriter |
