   243	
   244	<threat_model>
   245	## Trust Boundaries
   246	
   247	| Boundary | Description |
   248	|----------|-------------|
   249	| RAW file → writer | Vendor binary scan data (masses/intensities) crosses into our arrays |
   250	| writer → Parquet/ZIP | Numeric arrays serialized to on-disk facets read by external readers |
   251	
   252	## STRIDE Threat Register
   253	
   254	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   255	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   256	| T-02-01 | Tampering | per-spectrum m/z sort | mitigate | Stable (mz,intensity) sort; NUnit Task-3 (a) asserts multiset preserved (no drop/merge) under duplicate m/z |
   257	| T-02-02 | Information disclosure | f64→f32 intensity narrowing | accept | Lossy narrowing is the declared canonical width (DATA-02); Phase-4 records the transform for L2 round-trip tolerance |
   258	| T-02-03 | Denial of service | full-array accumulation for large RAW | mitigate | Reference cadence is ParquetSpectrumWriter's 1,048,576-point row-group flush; Task 1 either implements per-row-group flushing (spectra kept whole) or records the deferral rationale in SUMMARY |
   259	| T-02-04 | Tampering | centroid/profile routing | mitigate | Route on explicit `MZData.isCentroided` (the representation flag), never inferred from array shape — matches MzMlSpectrumWriter |
   260	| T-02-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | n/a | No new package installs in this phase; all deps from Phase 1 |
   261	</threat_model>
   262	
   263	<verification>
   264	- Build green: `DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=LatestMajor DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD_TO_PRERELEASE=1 dotnet build -c Release`.
   265	- Full NUnit suite green via the Rosetta x64 runtime: `DOTNET_ROOT_X64=$HOME/.dotnet-x64 dotnet test -c Release` (no existing tests broken; new MzPeakWriterTests pass).
   266	- Convert small.RAW and run the conformance oracle:
   267	  `arch -x86_64 ~/.dotnet-x64/dotnet ThermoRawFileParser/bin/Release/net8.0/ThermoRawFileParser.dll -i ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/Data/small.RAW -o <out> -f mzpeak`
   268	  then `mzpeak-validate <out>/small.mzpeak` — the `mz_monotonic_data` INFO is resolved
   269	  (sorting_rank=0) and NO new errors appear beyond the still-expected Phase-3 `scan`-facet error.
   270	- Differential lightweight check: spectra_data row count == sum of per-spectrum point counts
   271	  TRFP reads for small.RAW; per-spectrum point counts and the (mz,intensity) multiset match
   272	  within f32 tolerance.
   273	</verification>
   274	
   275	<success_criteria>
   276	Phase Definition-of-Done — maps to the four ROADMAP success criteria:
   277	
   278	1. **DATA-01 (point layout):** `spectra_data.parquet` written as
   279	   `point: struct<spectrum_index:u64, mz:f64, intensity:f32>`, one row per data point,
   280	   contiguous per spectrum, for all in-range spectra. → Task 1; verified by row-count and
   281	   schema assertions.
   282	2. **DATA-02 (widths + sort + multiset):** mz coerced f64, intensity f32; per-spectrum m/z
   283	   ascending via a stable sort that preserves the (mz,intensity) multiset (no drop/merge).
   284	   → Task 1 (emit) + Task 3 (NUnit locks); verified by ascending + multiset + leaf-type tests.
   285	3. **DATA-03 (centroid facet):** when a centroid representation exists (isCentroided),
   286	   centroid peaks are written to `spectra_peaks.parquet` (mz f64 / intensity f32) and listed in
   287	   `mzpeak_index.json` only when written. → Task 2; verified by presence + index + schema check.
   288	4. **DATA-04 (filters honored):** MS-level (MsLevel/MaxLevel) and scan-range filters honored;
   289	   filtered-out spectra produce zero rows in every facet and are not counted. → Task 1 (loop
   290	   gating) + Task 3 (MS2-only filter test); verified by the filtered-run NUnit assertion.
   291	
   292	Plus: `spectrum_count` and per-facet point counts in CustomMetadata reflect real totals;
   293	`sorting_rank:0` declared on `point.mz` resolving the Phase-1 `mz_monotonic_data` INFO.
   294	
   295	## Risks
   296	- **Non-stable / value-merging sort silently loses points** (T-02-01) — mitigated by an explicit
   297	  stable (mz,intensity) sort and the Task-3 multiset assertion. Note: base `ReadMZData` already
   298	  Array.Sorts by m/z but ties are not guaranteed stable, hence the extra stable pass.
   299	- **f64→f32 intensity narrowing is lossy** (T-02-02) — accepted as the declared canonical width;
   300	  Phase 4 records the transform for L2 tolerance.
   301	- **Memory blow-up on large RAW** (T-02-03) — reference cadence is the existing 1,048,576-point
   302	  row-group flush; Task 1 implements batching (spectra kept whole) or records deferral rationale.
   303	- **Centroid routing inferred from shape rather than the representation flag** (T-02-04) —
   304	  mitigated by routing strictly on `MZData.isCentroided`.
   305	
   306	## Dependencies
   307	- **Phase 1 (01-01):** `MzPeakParquet` helper (Column/WriteAsync/BuildParamField/CvColumn), the
   308	  existing `WriteFacet`/`AddStored`/`Leaf`/`SpectrumArrayIndex` scaffolding in
   309	  `MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs`, the STORED-zip + ZSTD pipeline, and the x64-pinned build with the
   310	  Rosetta `~/.dotnet-x64` run/test runtime.
   311	- **Inherited `SpectrumWriter.ReadMZData`** for per-scan profile/centroid reads and the
   312	  `ParseInput` MsLevel/MaxLevel/NoPeakPicking filters.
   313	- **External tooling for verification only** (not shipped): x64 .NET 8 runtime at `~/.dotnet-x64`,
   314	  `python3.11` with `pyarrow`, and `mzpeak-validate`.
   315	</success_criteria>
